OL,5, Doctors belonging to ethnic minorities 
OL,6, were "less likely to speak up" when    
OL,7, given unsuitable personal protective   
OL,8, equipment, the Covid inquiry has heard.
OL,10,FProf Philip Banfield, who chairs the   
OL,11,FBritish Medical Association, added     
OL,12,Ftwo-thirds of doctors felt they had not
OL,13,Fbeen given a proper risk assessment    
OL,15,FEthnic minorities were significantly   
OL,16,Fmore likely than white British people  
OL,17,Fto both catch and die of Covid.        
OL,19,FBangladeshi, Pakistani and Caribbean   
OL,20,Fbackgrounds were particularly affected.
